node.text: Loneliness, sadness… we talk about these feelings a lot during the holidays—especially this year—but those feelings can happen any time of year to any type of person. The good news is there are proven ways to move through those feelings and feel better. If you’ve ever struggled with isolation, I know the feeling. That’s why I’m partnering with @SanvelloHealth: it’s an app with day-by-day guides on how to feel better, tools to get you through tough moments, plus therapy and coaching. We’ve got a few things cooking, but if you need help now, download Sanvello. It’s private, it’s confidential, and it can help. #SanvelloPartner

node.text: I’m excited to join @offoutdoors and @happy_camper_live to help bring summer camp to your backyard. I’ll be teaching you and your family how to spot planets, stars and satellites with just your own eyes and a little bit of imagination. Stargazing is a fun outdoor activity the whole family can do together at night – just make sure to remember to first apply OFF! Deep Woods® spray for long lasting protection from pesky biting bugs that might try to get in on the fun too! Check out the link in my bio for more. #BackyardSummerCamp #ad

Astronaut Scott Kelly hosts Bedtime Storytime with his former colleague Astronaut Leland Melvin. @lelandmelvin , author of Chasing Space, reads his online children's short stories and answers audience questions about space and life in isolation in space and on Earth.

node.title: Bedtime Storytime with Astronaut Scott Kelly & Friends

node.text: Astronaut Scott Kelly hosts Bedtime Storytime with his astronaut classmate and former colleague Astronaut Mike Massimino. Massimino reads an excerpt from his new young readers' book Spaceman.

node.title: Bedtime Storytime with Astronaut Scott Kelly & Friends

node.text: Astronaut Scott Kelly hosts Bedtime Storytime with his twin brother Mark Kelly. The AstroTwins read Mark Kelly's children's book Mousetronaut together.

node.title: Bedtime Storytime with AstroTwins Mark and Scott Kelly

node.text:
READ TOGETHER, BE TOGETHER is a nationwide movement developed by Penguin Random House in partnership with Parents magazine that celebrates the importance, and power, of the shared reading experience between an adult and a child. 
Your favorite authors & celebrities hosted a LIVE virtual story time to share stories with kids and families.

Astronaut Scott Kelly reads MY JOURNEY TO THE STARS to children around the world as families across the globe STAY Home to Save Lives.

node.text:
Ready for launch? 🚀 

Counting down to liftoff of my latest book, sharing 10 life-changing moments from my path to space and how the lessons I learned can help launch your own goals, career or aspirations in life here on Earth. 

Here’s a sneak peak of my new book cover!

Excited to announce the on sale date is 4/12/22. Countdown clock has begun. 🕰 

Available for pre-order now! 
🚀 Link in bio! 🚀 

#booklaunch #yearinspace #astronaut

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by SCOTT KELLY on July 25, 2021. May be an image of airplane and outdoors.

node.text: Dale “Snort” Snodgrass was killed yesterday in a small plane crash. I had the pleasure of knowing him and even flying with him in an F-14 with a new flight control system with me in the backseat which felt oddly appropriate. A true legend. #RIP Snort.

node.text: Godspeed Wally Funk and those other guys! Was great to catch another historic launch. Also, great to see two brothers in space together… Congrats to @blueorigin team and entire crew on your successful spaceflight today!

user.full_name: I N F I N I T E  W O N D E R 🌎

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by SCOTT KELLY in Mount Bierstadt with @amikokelly, and @stationcdrkelly. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and outdoors.

node.text:
In space I enjoyed looking down at rugged mountain ranges below. Yesterday, I got a new perspective, although from a lower altitude, but the highest I’ve ever climbed here on Earth. 

My wife,@amikokelly, and I celebrating our anniversary on Mt. Bierstadt at 14,065’!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by SCOTT KELLY on July 11, 2021. May be an image of text.

node.text:
Congratulations to @richardbranson & @virgingalactic on today’s historic test flight—launching a new era in space tourism! 

The orbital perspective is real. Pushing boundaries for more people to experience it elevates humanity on Earth.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by SCOTT KELLY on July 04, 2021. May be an image of standing.

node.text:
One of the great things about being an astronaut and flying in space was being a part of something greater than oneself.

Same holds true about being a U.S. Citizen. Happy #FourthOfJuly!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by SCOTT KELLY in Galveston, Texas. May be an image of body of water.

node.text:
Recognizing #Juneteenth  today as not only a national holiday to celebrate—at last—but also a time to reflect on our nation’s promise to protect its humanity. May we learn from our history’s dark past and work together to now end racism once and for all. 

Galveston from ISS, 2015

Michael Collins as Command Module Pilot for #Apollo11 was the best spaceflight assignment ever made. His grace, humility & professionalism made him perfect for the historic role and cemented his legacy. 

I enjoyed the few moments we shared together. #RIP, @astromichaelcollins.
